  dynamic server-side websites with Node.js.` }) -%>

  <div class="column gap">
    <div class="column-content">
      <h1>Creating Modular EJS Templates</h1>
      <p>
        Modular design in EJS involves breaking down your website into reusable
        pieces, often stored in separate files. This can include things like
        headers, footers, and any other reusable markup. EJS's include function
        allows you to include these pieces in your main EJS files, promoting
        code reuse and organization.
      </p>
      <div class="column-footer">
        <img
          class="column-footer-image"
          src="/lab4/images/column-footer.webp"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <%- include('column', { title: 'Modular CSS in EJS', content: ` Just like with
